reviews.review: A Star Wars movie is always a must see. Under the circumstances after the disaster that The Last Jedi (and The Force Awakens) was, it was almost impossible to create an end to a pointless story so I think J.J. achieves to deliver an acceptable movie with many many plot holes and inconsistencies because of what I said before, but still enjoyable. This saga lost its magic and power due to a poor handling of this trilogy so I recommend you to lower your expectations and to be comprehensive so you can enjoy the movie.
This was a great ending for the trilogy, but it suffered from the problems of ttis saga.
Not a good conclusion to 9 movies they trying to do to much with not enough time
Felt like a marvel movie. Better than 7 and 8, though. Most of the mistakes felt like they were trying to repair what happened in the 8th movie. Very glad Rose got limited screen time.

Good not great, does better than the two films prior to it at being original yet also satisfying but falls short of being the methodically crafted and epic finale I expected. Abrams does a great job at salvaging what Johnson left for him in my opinion but the mistake of not giving all three movies to the same director definitely left its mark on Rise of Skywalker and not in the best of ways. Aside from the that and all of the twists which for most part I could see coming from a mile away, I'd say Rise of Skywalker is definitely worth your time, in order to put an end to this flawed yet not terrible trilogy.
it completed the storyline.  that's about it

Finn was the best part of this film and that's why I give it a star. The first half was fine. Then any scene with Rey and Kylo together just made me cringe and one of the twists at the end made me audibly gag out loud during my showing.
Yikes. Very clich√©, but how do you conquer a series built up in just that amount of time? Took a shot for the fences. Just not to my liking.

If you are true child of the 70s and 80s and grew up with the original trilogy. You will love this movie insight of a few things. Those things aren't this movies fault there the last movies fault. I go to movies like this as an adult because it is an escape a FANTASY NOT REALITY and a call back to my youth. I Got that with the force awakens and I totally got that with this. I didnt get into the venom and debate of The Last Jedi  I'll just say instead of a middle picture that is supposed to continue to set up the overall story and set up the Final act of a trilogy it didnt it was basically like a second 1st movie it also totally wasted Mark Hamil and did poo poo on Luke skywalker that being said the biggest thing I took away after watching this movie is it also missed golden opportunity of having three leads together before final movie. All in all JJ Abrams did wonders with course correcting and trying things up.  Yes would have liked to seen what he would have done if the middle picture wouldn't have been so drastic but he is brilliant and I felt like I was back in A star wars movie. A+
Satisfying end to the Skywalker saga. Left the theater pleased
